The paper deals with a method for dimensionality reduction of high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization algorithms and matrix computations, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm on a specific dataset, which is related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
